ontologyFramework.OFEventManagement.OFEventImplementation.OFEventProcedure

Class HasBooleanTrue

  • java.lang.Object
    • ontologyFramework.OFEventManagement.OFEventImplementation.OFEventProcedure.HasBooleanTrue
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.io.Serializable, OFEventInterface

    public class HasBooleanTrue
extends java.lang.Object
implements OFEventInterface
    This class implement the event that takes as input : ...( OWLNamedIndividual ind, OWLDataProperty prop). Which return true if the individual has that property and false otherwise. In the ontology an event must be defined which belongs to the class "OFEvent" thus has the properties: 
     
        implementsOFEventName "ontologyFramework.OFEventManagement.OFEventImplementation.OFEventProcedure.HasBooleanValue"^^string
  &
  hasEvent definition 
  		"in:ontologyFramework.OFEventManagement.OFEventImplementation.OFEventParameter.
			 ?a exc.AsOWLIndividual
			 ?b hasExceptionNotify.AsOWLDataProperty
			 !r HasBooleanTrue( ?a ?b)"^^strign
    So, isCorrectInput(List) return true if inputs.get( 0).getParameter() instanceof OWLNamedIndividual and inputs.get( 1).getParameter() instanceof OWLObjectProperty and inputs.get( 0).getOntoRef() are true. The evaluateEvent(List, OFBuildedListInvoker) just uses the invoker.getClassFromList( "MappersList", "Boolean") the get the boolean mapper and check if the value is true.
